Walker (1871) , Peyerimhoff (1907) , Alfieri (1976) , and Salman (1996) reported the occurrence of
L. minutus
in Egypt . The species is common and widely distributed throughout the northern Palearctic region, especially in Europe and central and northern Asia (Gentili and Chiesa 1976; Hansen 1987 , 1999 ;
Fikáček et al. 2015
; Przewoźny and Fikáček 2016). The species is absent from Africa ( Hansen 1999 ; Hebauer 2006 ;
Fikáček et al. 2015
).

